==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Amphidromical
<hw>Am`phi*drom"ic*al</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>'amfi`dromos</grk> running about or around.]</ety> <def>Pertaining
to an Attic festival at the naming of a child; -- so called because the
friends of the parents <xex>carried</xex> the child <xex>around</xex>
the hearth and then named it.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Amphigamous</ent>⟦br⟧
